  "A school fundraiser sells candy bars for $2 and popcorn bags for $3. They sold 150 items and made $370. How many candy bars were sold?": "",
  "70": "",
  "80": "",
  "60": "",
  "90": "",
  "c + p = 150 and 2c + 3p = 370. Substitute p = 150 - c: 2c + 450 - 3c = 370 → -c = -80 → c = 80.": "",
  "A nurse mixes a 10% saline solution with a 40% saline solution to create 600 mL of a 20% solution. How many mL of the 10% solution are needed?": "",
  "500 mL": "",
  "300 mL": "",
  "400 mL": "",
  "200 mL": "",
  "x + y = 600 and 0.10x + 0.40y = 120. Substitute y = 600 - x: 0.10x + 240 - 0.40x = 120 → -0.30x = -120 → x = 400 mL.": "",
  "A company produces widgets at $5 per unit with $200 fixed costs. They sell widgets for $8 each. How many widgets must be sold to break even?": "",
  "50": "",
  "100": "",
  "67": "",
  "40": "",
  "Cost = 5n + 200, Revenue = 8n. Break even: 8n = 5n + 200 → 3n = 200 → n = 66.7, so 67 widgets (round up since you cannot sell partial widgets).": "",
  "A family drives to the beach at 60 mph and returns at 40 mph. The total trip takes 5 hours. How far is the beach?": "",
  "200 miles": "",
  "120 miles": "",
  "150 miles": "",
  "100 miles": "",
  "Let d = distance. Time there: d/60, time back: d/40. d/60 + d/40 = 5. LCD = 120: 2d + 3d = 600 → 5d = 600 → d = 120 miles.": "",
  "A theater charges $12 for adults and $7 for seniors. If 300 people attend and total revenue is $2,850, how many seniors attended?": "",
  "150": "",
  "170": "",
  "120": "",
  "130": "",
  "a + s = 300 and 12a + 7s = 2850. Substitute a = 300 - s: 3600 - 12s + 7s = 2850 → -5s = -750 → s = 150.": "",
  "Two trains leave the same station traveling in opposite directions. One goes 50 mph and the other 70 mph. After how many hours are they 360 miles apart?": "",
  "3 hours": "",
  "5 hours": "",
  "4 hours": "",
  "2 hours": "",
  "Combined speed = 50 + 70 = 120 mph. Distance = rate x time: 360 = 120t → t = 3 hours.": "",
  "A caterer charges $15/person for meal A and $20/person for meal B. If 60 guests attend and total food cost is $1,050, how many chose meal A?": "",
  "35": "",
  "a + b = 60 and 15a + 20b = 1050. Substitute b = 60 - a: 15a + 1200 - 20a = 1050 → -5a = -150 → a = 30.": "",
